   "body" : "Currently `dumpwallet` (and other RPCs that create server-side files) can scribble all over the file system, at least as the user running `bitcoind` permits.\r\n\r\nIt would be better if these were at the least limited to the data directory, or even a specific directory within the data directory, say, `~/.bitcoin/dumpwallet`âto avoid name collisions with wallets, lock files and database files. Overwriting is already prevented.\r\n\r\n(Issue originally reported by Florian Mathieu)",
